HEADWORD: Fair-haired
<hw>Fair"-haired`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having fair or light-colored hair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>favorite; considered especially talented or
promising; <as>as, the <ex>fair-haired</ex> boy of the literary
set</as>.</def> <mark>[prenominal]</mark> <mark>[informal]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> blue-eyed(prenominal), white-haired(prenominal),
white-headed.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fairhood</ent>⟦br⟧
